<br>
Pet chaining trades time for mana.  Fights take long, but less mana is used per fight.  Indeed, chaining pets, I can wind up with <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>more</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> mana at the end of many fights than I started with.  In contrast, sustain pet and nuke is a much more mana intense tactic, but leads to shorter fights.  Sometimes chaining is more appropriate.  Other times, sustain and nuke.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  If you have 15/20 Magicians say they dont want to chaincast...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Not only isn't this a voting matter, but you are likely wrong as well.  There are probably more 50+ pet chaining mages than not.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  So why not scrap Chaincast all together?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I will give up chain casting pets when they pry the malachite from my cold dead hands.<br>
<br>
You're telling me that one of my best tactics is wrong because you don't like it and you don't use it?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Why do we need to buff our pets up with BO4 + Muzzle if we are going to chaincast.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Uhm, because sometimes buffing up a pet is appropriate?  And sometimes it is not?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Immlazen:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I was giving those spells to use, so a pet heal comparable to other pet classes will make more sense so we dont have to rebuff the pet.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Oh poor baby.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &quot;I don't wanna rebuff my pet, I wanna better heal!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Deciding exactly how to spend your mana, and whether to buff your pet or not is just part of being a mage.<br>
<br>
That said, I want to emphasize that chaining pets should not generally required, but an option.  Sometimes even the best option.  Sometimes.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Zyrexx:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I will not chain cast as that is not what we were ment to do.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Uhm, just how do you know this?  Really?  Sure, it can be your choice as a mage not to use this tactic, but refusing to ever employ one of the best tactics available to a mage is just handicapping yourself.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>had</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> the opportunity to discourage chain casting, and they did the exact opposite.  They increased the raw power of pets, instead of adding the strength through new buffs and summoned items, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> added multiple AA skills that support that tactic.<br>
<br>
Guess what.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Zyrexx:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Chain casting should not be our only option ever.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I don't understand.  Because there is one powerful tactic you do not like it should never be the best or only solution for any encounter at all?  That's pretty narrow minded.  Chain casting should not be the only viable tactic, but can there be fights and situations where that is the best and maybe even only solution?  Why not?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Finraziel:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  But being told by a 53 mage how the &quot;high level&quot; game is supposed to be played at 60+ with 100aaxp and that we have nothing to worry about is laughable.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Noonie:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  i really do resent unexperianced karnors exp group mages telling us to &quot;stop whining because we are ruining the class&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Careful, you two, and especially <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Noonie</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Everyone is entitled to their opinion, and anyone can reason about the class based on a combination of their direct experience and reading.  If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Yanbun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is wrong, please limit yourself to specific arguments.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Noonie:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  if anyones going to ruin the class, its going to be level 51 know-it-all's telling vi we are fine or overpowered in beta, when they have little experiance with the spells we use all the time...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>exactly</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> what I do not want to see from you again <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Noonie</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  You will <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>inform</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> him of how he he wrong, you will <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> simply insult him.  Reason, not emotion.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Alucard:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  just curious on how you mods are functioning here...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, yesterday I went to see a movie, so I did not moderate hardly at all.  I am generally loathe to lock threads I am advocating a position, and finally, what is unacceptable to me is a cycle of the same stupid arguments spiralling out of control.  So far as I can tell, there was been one exchange of salvos, and no spiral.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b