<br>
I am not taking a stand on ratios and recast times.  The arguments I see are generally over simplified to the point of distortion, and I remain dubious about the conclusions so reached.<br>
<br>
However, the issue that interests me from this thread is this:<br>
<br>
Whereas chaining pets should not become the sole viable tactic for 61+ mages, chaining pets is properly a legitimate tactic of mages.  If PoP forces pet chaining in almost all encounters, that is a weak design and hurts mages.  Since the main alternative to chaining pets is sustain and nuke, spells and abilities should be added or upgraded so that sustain and nuke is a viable choice for a significant number of encounters.  This most likely means improvements to mage pet heals.<br>
<br>
This is a bigger issue than just PoP.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
